2b:["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","faq-0",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"Will my customers be annoyed by speaking to AI?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Modern AI voices are natural and professional. In our surveys, 89% of callers do not realise they are speaking to AI, and most appreciate the quick, efficient service. The alternative for most trades is voicemail or phone tag — both of which customers find far more frustrating."}]]}],["$","div","faq-1",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"Can AI handle angry or emotional callers?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes. AI is actually better suited to difficult callers than tired humans — it never gets frustrated, never raises its voice, and always remains professional. For genuinely complex situations, it can escalate to a callback from you."}]]}],["$","div","faq-2",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"What if I already have a part-time receptionist?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"AI complements human receptionists perfectly. The human handles calls during work hours; the AI covers evenings, weekends, lunch breaks, and busy periods. Many businesses use both — the AI as backup and overflow coverage."}]]}],["$","div","faq-3",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"Can the AI sound like someone from my local area?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes. whoza.ai offers multiple voice options including regional accents. You can also customise the greeting, script, and tone to match your brand — whether that is formal and corporate or friendly and local."}]]}],["$","div","faq-4",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"How quickly can I switch from voicemail to AI?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Setup takes 30 minutes. You can go from missing calls to having an AI receptionist answering them in under an hour. The 7-day free trial lets you test before making any commitment."}]]}],["$","div","faq-5",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"Is AI really cheaper than a human receptionist?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Dramatically cheaper. A human receptionist costs £26,000-£35,000 in year one including salary, NI, pension, and overheads. AI costs £708-£4,788 per year. The savings are £21,000-£30,000 annually — enough for a new work van or a full marketing budget."}]]}]]}]]}]
